Leading international think-tank, the Club of Rome is set to hold its global Summit for the first time in South Africa. The summit will see the gathering of notable scientists, economists, business people and former heads of state to discuss South Africa and Africa’s economic landscape, climate change and new models of finance. Joining CNBC Africa for more are the co-Presidents of the Club of Rome, Sandrine Dixson-Declève and Dr Mamphela Ramphele.